[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 7141,
        "end_time": 8905,
        "text": "Ah, romantic love -"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 8905,
        "end_time": 10839,
        "text": "beautiful and intoxicating,"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 10839,
        "end_time": 13259,
        "text": "heartbreaking and soul-crushing,"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 13259,
        "end_time": 15357,
        "text": "often all at the same time."
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 15357,
        "end_time": 18919,
        "text": "Why do we choose to put ourselves\nthrough its emotional wringer?"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 18919,
        "end_time": 21201,
        "text": "Does love make our lives meaningful,"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 21201,
        "end_time": 24444,
        "text": "or is it an escape from our loneliness\nand suffering?"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 24444,
        "end_time": 26705,
        "text": "Is love a disguise for our sexual desire,"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 26705,
        "end_time": 30409,
        "text": "or a trick of biology\nto make us procreate?"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 30409,
        "end_time": 32337,
        "text": "Is it all we need?"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 32337,
        "end_time": 34558,
        "text": "Do we need it at all?"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 34558,
        "end_time": 36365,
        "text": "If romantic love has a purpose,"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 36365,
        "end_time": 39965,
        "text": "neither science nor psychology\nhas discovered it yet."
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 39965,
        "end_time": 41453,
        "text": "But over the course of history,"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 41453,
        "end_time": 46866,
        "text": "some of our most respected philosophers\nhave put forward some intriguing theories."
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 46866,
        "end_time": 49728,
        "text": "Love makes us whole, again."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 49728,
        "end_time": 51523,
        "text": "The ancient Greek philosopher Plato"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 51523,
        "end_time": 55654,
        "text": "explored the idea that we love\nin order to become complete."
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 55654,
        "end_time": 58298,
        "text": "In his &quot;Symposium&quot;,\nhe wrote about a dinner party,"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 58298,
        "end_time": 61050,
        "text": "at which Aristophanes, a comic playwright,"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 61050,
        "end_time": 64298,
        "text": "regales the guests \nwith the following story:"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 64298,
        "end_time": 70735,
        "text": "humans were once creatures with four arms,\nfour legs, and two faces."
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 70735,
        "end_time": 72803,
        "text": "One day, they angered the gods,"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 72803,
        "end_time": 76377,
        "text": "and Zeus sliced them all in two."
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 76377,
        "end_time": 81368,
        "text": "Since then, every person has been missing\nhalf of him or herself."
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 81368,
        "end_time": 86253,
        "text": "Love is the longing to find a soulmate\nwho&#39;ll make us feel whole again,"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 86253,
        "end_time": 91918,
        "text": "or, at least, that&#39;s what Plato believed\na drunken comedian would say at a party."
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 91918,
        "end_time": 94970,
        "text": "Love tricks us into having babies."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 94970,
        "end_time": 98199,
        "text": "Much, much later, German philosopher\nArthur Schopenhauer"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 98199,
        "end_time": 101155,
        "text": "maintained that love \nbased in sexual desire"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 101155,
        "end_time": 103734,
        "text": "was a voluptuous illusion."
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 103734,
        "end_time": 107113,
        "text": "He suggested that we love because\nour desires lead us to believe"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 107113,
        "end_time": 112165,
        "text": "that another person will make us happy,\nbut we are sorely mistaken."
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 112165,
        "end_time": 114330,
        "text": "Nature is tricking us into procreating,"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 114330,
        "end_time": 118698,
        "text": "and the loving fusion we seek\nis consummated in our children."
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 118698,
        "end_time": 120662,
        "text": "When our sexual desires are satisfied,"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 120662,
        "end_time": 124102,
        "text": "we are thrown back \ninto our tormented existences,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 124102,
        "end_time": 126933,
        "text": "and we succeed only in maintaining\nthe species"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 126933,
        "end_time": 131215,
        "text": "and perpetuating the cycle \nof human drudgery."
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 131215,
        "end_time": 133504,
        "text": "Sounds like somebody needs a hug."
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 133504,
        "end_time": 136559,
        "text": "Love is escape from our loneliness."
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 136559,
        "end_time": 140397,
        "text": "According to the Nobel Prize-winning\nBritish philosopher Bertrand Russell,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 140397,
        "end_time": 144614,
        "text": "we love in order to quench\nour physical and psychological desires."
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 144614,
        "end_time": 147180,
        "text": "Humans are designed to procreate,"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 147180,
        "end_time": 149984,
        "text": "but without the ecstasy \nof passionate love,"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 149984,
        "end_time": 152369,
        "text": "sex is unsatisfying."
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 152369,
        "end_time": 156464,
        "text": "Our fear of the cold, cruel world\ntempts us to build hard shells"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 156464,
        "end_time": 158967,
        "text": "to protect and isolate ourselves."
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 158967,
        "end_time": 164697,
        "text": "Love&#39;s delight, intimacy, and warmth\nhelps us overcome our fear of the world,"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 164697,
        "end_time": 166309,
        "text": "escape our lonely shells,"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 166309,
        "end_time": 169235,
        "text": "and engage more abundantly in life."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 169235,
        "end_time": 174155,
        "text": "Love enriches our whole being,\nmaking it the best thing in life."
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 174155,
        "end_time": 176664,
        "text": "Love is a misleading affliction."
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 176664,
        "end_time": 177908,
        "text": "Siddh\u0101rtha Gautama,"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 177908,
        "end_time": 180487,
        "text": "who became known as the Buddha,\nor the Enlightened One,"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 180487,
        "end_time": 184001,
        "text": "probably would have had some interesting\narguments with Russell."
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 184001,
        "end_time": 188992,
        "text": "Buddha proposed that we love because\nwe are trying to satisfy our base desires."
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 188992,
        "end_time": 192635,
        "text": "Yet, our passionate cravings are defects,"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 192635,
        "end_time": 197346,
        "text": "and attachments, even romantic love,\nare a great source of suffering."
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 197346,
        "end_time": 200137,
        "text": "Luckily, Buddha discovered \nthe eight-fold path,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 200137,
        "end_time": 203479,
        "text": "a sort of program for \nextinguishing the fires of desire"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 203479,
        "end_time": 205642,
        "text": "so that we can reach Nirvana,"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 205642,
        "end_time": 210560,
        "text": "an enlightened state of peace, clarity,\nwisdom, and compassion."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 210560,
        "end_time": 214199,
        "text": "The novelist Cao Xueqin illustrated\nthis Buddhist sentiment"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 214199,
        "end_time": 219182,
        "text": "that romantic love is folly in \none of China&#39;s greatest classical novels,"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 219182,
        "end_time": 221900,
        "text": "&quot;Dream of the Red Chamber.&quot;"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 221900,
        "end_time": 225370,
        "text": "In a subplot, Jia Rui \nfalls in love with Xi-feng"
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 225370,
        "end_time": 227680,
        "text": "who tricks and humiliates him."
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 227680,
        "end_time": 231293,
        "text": "Conflicting emotions of love and hate\ntear him apart,"
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 231293,
        "end_time": 235159,
        "text": "so a Taoist gives him a magic mirror\nthat can cure him"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 235159,
        "end_time": 237765,
        "text": "as long as he doesn&#39;t \nlook at the front of it."
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 237765,
        "end_time": 240370,
        "text": "But of course, \nhe looks at the front of it."
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 240370,
        "end_time": 242278,
        "text": "He sees Xi-feng."
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 242278,
        "end_time": 243878,
        "text": "His soul enters the mirror"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 243878,
        "end_time": 248715,
        "text": "and he is dragged away \nin iron chains to die."
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 248715,
        "end_time": 252372,
        "text": "Not all Buddhists think this way\nabout romantic and erotic love,"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 252372,
        "end_time": 253985,
        "text": "but the moral of this story"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 253985,
        "end_time": 257045,
        "text": "is that such attachments\nspell tragedy,"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 257045,
        "end_time": 260901,
        "text": "and should, along with magic mirrors,\nbe avoided."
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 260901,
        "end_time": 264092,
        "text": "Love lets us reach beyond ourselves."
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 264092,
        "end_time": 266899,
        "text": "Let&#39;s end on a slightly \nmore positive note."
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 266899,
        "end_time": 269048,
        "text": "The French philosopher Simone de Beauvoir"
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 269048,
        "end_time": 272934,
        "text": "proposed that love is the desire\nto integrate with another"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 272934,
        "end_time": 275652,
        "text": "and that it infuses our lives\nwith meaning."
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 275652,
        "end_time": 278515,
        "text": "However, she was less \nconcerned with why we love"
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 278515,
        "end_time": 282463,
        "text": "and more interested \nin how we can love better."
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 282463,
        "end_time": 285780,
        "text": "She saw that the problem\nwith traditional romantic love"
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 285780,
        "end_time": 287552,
        "text": "is it can be so captivating,"
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 287552,
        "end_time": 291294,
        "text": "that we are tempted to make it\nour only reason for being."
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 291294,
        "end_time": 294800,
        "text": "Yet, dependence on another \nto justify our existence"
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 294800,
        "end_time": 298684,
        "text": "easily leads to boredom and power games."
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 298684,
        "end_time": 302518,
        "text": "To avoid this trap, Beauvoir advised\nloving authentically,"
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 302518,
        "end_time": 304937,
        "text": "which is more like a great friendship."
    },
    {
        "index": 94,
        "start_time": 304937,
        "end_time": 307933,
        "text": "Lovers support each other \nin discovering themselves,"
    },
    {
        "index": 95,
        "start_time": 307933,
        "end_time": 309767,
        "text": "reaching beyond themselves,"
    },
    {
        "index": 96,
        "start_time": 309767,
        "end_time": 313463,
        "text": "and enriching their lives\nand the world together."
    },
    {
        "index": 97,
        "start_time": 313463,
        "end_time": 316558,
        "text": "Though we might never know\nwhy we fall in love,"
    },
    {
        "index": 98,
        "start_time": 316558,
        "end_time": 320548,
        "text": "we can be certain that it will be\nan emotional rollercoaster ride."
    },
    {
        "index": 99,
        "start_time": 320548,
        "end_time": 322259,
        "text": "It&#39;s scary and exhilarating."
    },
    {
        "index": 100,
        "start_time": 322259,
        "end_time": 323257,
        "text": "It makes us suffer"
    },
    {
        "index": 101,
        "start_time": 323257,
        "end_time": 325145,
        "text": "and makes us soar."
    },
    {
        "index": 102,
        "start_time": 325145,
        "end_time": 326667,
        "text": "Maybe we lose ourselves."
    },
    {
        "index": 103,
        "start_time": 326667,
        "end_time": 328238,
        "text": "Maybe we find ourselves."
    },
    {
        "index": 104,
        "start_time": 328238,
        "end_time": 329724,
        "text": "It might be heartbreaking,"
    },
    {
        "index": 105,
        "start_time": 329724,
        "end_time": 332557,
        "text": "or it might just be \nthe best thing in life."
    },
    {
        "index": 106,
        "start_time": 332557,
        "end_time": 334511,
        "text": "Will you dare to find out?"
    }
]